The wise man works with all those powers of a perfect soul, the union of which forms a beautiful harmony3 the unwise man is impelled by external circum- stances3 the wise man follows solely the inward impulse of his noble nature which never allows him to go wrong, while the other acts under a law, the application of which is some· · times uncertain.
